summary:
The Security Council,
 Reaffirming previous resolutions and statements on the situation between Ethiopia and Eritrea, 
Stressing commitment to the peace process, including through UNMEE, 
Recalling the Algiers Agreements and the Boundary Commission's delimitation decision, 
 Noting concern at lack of progress in border demarcation, 
Expressing concern at Ethiopia's rejection of parts of the Boundary Commission's decision and lack of cooperation, 
 Expressing disappointment at Eritrea's refusal to engage with the Secretary-General's Special Envoy, 
1. Decides to extend UNMEE's mandate until 15 March 2005; 
2. Approves adjustments to UNMEE; 
3. Calls on both parties to cooperate with UNMEE; 
4. Takes note of positive developments, welcomes Ethiopia's decision on direct flights, and urges implementation; 
5. Stresses parties' responsibility for Algiers Agreement implementation; 
6. Calls on parties to cooperate with the Boundary Commission; 
7. Urges Ethiopia to reaffirm acceptance of the Boundary Commission's decision; 
8. Supports the Secretary-General's Special Envoy; 
9. Calls on Eritrea to engage with the Special Envoy; 
10. Decides to monitor parties' steps; 
11. Requests the Secretary-General to monitor and review UNMEE's mandate; 
12. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
